This code sets up the CONTEXT structure `RopVirtualProtectExecute` to call the VirtualProtect function with the specified parameters:

- `Rcx` is set to the base address of the image.
- `Rdx` is set to the size of the image.
- `R8` is set to `PAGE_EXECUTE_READ`, indicating that the memory block should be executable and readable.
- `R9` points to a variable where the previous protection attribute will be stored.

This ensures that the memory containing the code will be executable, allowing the subsequent timers to execute the ROP chain.

