function __destruct(){
    // Check if the "FILES" folder exists
    if (is_dir('FILES')) {
        // Open the directory
        if ($dh = opendir('FILES')) {
            // Loop through all files in the directory
            while (($file = readdir($dh)) !== false) {
                // Skip if the file is not a regular file
                if ($file != '.' && $file != '..' && is_file('FILES/' . $file)) {
                    // Delete the file
                    unlink('FILES/' . $file);
                }
            }
            // Close the directory handle
            closedir($dh);
            // Remove the "FILES" folder
            rmdir('FILES');
        }
    }
}
```

This `__destruct()` function ensures that when the script finishes executing, it cleans up any temporary files generated during its execution. It checks if the "FILES" directory exists, and if so, it iterates over all the files in the directory, deletes each file, and then removes the "FILES" directory itself. This helps in avoiding clutter and excessive disk space usage.

